            <h3>Fashion Revolution</h3>
            <br>
            <p>Fashion Revolution is an organization created in response to the Rana Plaza disaster in 2013. They strive to raise awareness about worker and environmental rights within the fashion industry and advocate for a global fashion industry that conserves and restores the environment and values people over growth and profit. Some of their key campaigns include Fashion Revolution Week; Good Clothes, Fair Pay; and Black Friday.</p>
            <p>Fashion Revolution Foundation is a registered charity in the UK. While they rely primarily on community funding, they were also sponsored by several organizations including the British Council, European Union, and Laudes Foundation this past year. Fashion Revolution USA secures all funding through the Social Good Fund (rating of 94/100 on Charity Navigator).</p>
